snippet.textDisplay: ..."On the very same night that JD allegedly assaulted AH, she invited James Franco over to the home she shared with JD"... I know if I had just been through such a terrifying ordeal at the hands of my partner or spouse, the last thing I'd have done would be to have another guy come over to visit me. I'd be far too petrified of my partner giving me another beating. Also, women who go through domestic abuse often go to extreme lengths to hide the fact that they're being victimised. The fear, shame & guilt often felt by the person concerned is usually too powerful to move beyond on their own & often,  as a result of this, women will live with their abuser for years before deciding to take action. Women like Amber Turd with her BS & lies, make it all the more difficult for genuine cases to come forward. It's cases like these that creates doubt & leaves women who are already living in a constant state of terror, all the more anxious about coming forward,  too afraid they wont be believed, protected & kept safe.
